===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[liturgia]]'', from {{AGr.}} [[λειτουργία]] < ''[[λειτ-]]'', from ''[[λαός]]'', '''people''' + ''[[-ουργός]]'' < [[ἔργον]], '''work''' (work of the people)

===Noun===
{{en-noun|liturgies}}

#A predetermined or [[prescribe]]d set of [[ritual]]s that are performed, usually by a [[religion]].  An official worship service of the Christian church.

